$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Excel\Options

The registry key `HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Software\Microsoft\Office\_version_\Excel\Options` specifies some options for
→ Microsoft/Office/Excel[Excel].
-
For the value of `_version_`, see → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version[→ Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version].

The following script can be used to change some values with → Windows/registry/reg[`reg`] in → Windows/cmd-exe[cmd.exe]:
gh|about-Windows-Registry|/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Microsoft/Office/application_version/Excel/Options/setOptions.bas||

{ DefaultCPG

  Apparently, `DefaultCPG` is supposed to specify the default codepage (for example when importing data into excel).

  The value 65001 means → development/Unicode/UTF-8[UTF-8].

}
{ DefaultFormat

 `DefaultFormat` specfies the default format in which Excel sheets are saved.

  Apparently, 52 (hex 34) corresponds to *xlsm*.

}
{ DeveloperTools #reg-excel-developer-tools

  If the value of `DeveloperTools` is set to 1, Excel → Microsoft/Office/Excel#excel-display-developer-tab[displays the developer tools] (which is required(?) to record macros).

}

